## Resources Needed

### Estimated Effort
- **Development**: 10-14 weeks (1 developer, full-time)
- **Testing**: 3-4 weeks (cross-platform, accessibility, E2E)
- **Documentation**: 2 weeks (setup, migration, user guide)

### Skills Required
- Frontend development (Next.js 14, React 18, TypeScript)
- Firebase/Firestore (real-time sync, security rules)
- Capacitor (desktop/mobile plugins, native builds)
- Web Audio API
- Accessibility engineering (WCAG, ARIA, screen readers)
- Cross-platform testing and debugging
- Python → TypeScript porting experience

### Tools & Infrastructure
- **Frontend**: Next.js 14 (App Router), React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- **Backend**: Firebase (Firestore, Auth, Functions)
- **Desktop/Mobile**: Capacitor 5, Electron (desktop wrapper)
- **Testing**: Vitest, Playwright, axe-core, Jest
- **State Management**: React Context + Firestore (no additional library needed)
- **Storage**: Firestore (cloud), IndexedDB (local cache via localForage)
- **Deployment**: Vercel (web), Capacitor (desktop/mobile builds)
- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions
- **Analytics**: Firebase Analytics (privacy-respecting)

### Budget
- **Development**: ~100-160 hours (1 FTE for 2.5-3.5 months)
- **Testing**: ~24-32 hours
- **Firebase**: Free tier sufficient initially (1GB Firestore, 50K reads/day)
- **Hosting**: Vercel free tier (web), Capacitor builds free
- **Tools**: All open-source, no licensing costs

